834/http://www.ose.or.jp/e/profile/5465 |date=2015-02-07 }}.\" [[Osaka Securities Exchange|Osaka Exchange Inc.]]. Retrieved on February 7, 2015.</ref>\n*[[Resona Bank]] - Bingomachi<ref>\"[http://www.resona-gr.co.jp/holdings/english/about/outline/office.html UHead Office Location - Osaka Head Office].\" [[Resona Bank]]. Retrieved on April 15, 2014.</ref>\n*[[Sakura Color Products|Sakura Color Products Corporation]] - Morinomiya<ref>\"[http://www.craypas.com/global/aboutsakura/profile.html Corporate Profile].\" [[Sakura Color Products Corporation]]. Retrieved on February 7, 2015.</ref>\n*[[Shionogi]] - Dojomachi<ref>\"[http://www.shionogi.co.jp/en/company/outline/index.html Company Profile].\" [[Shionogi]]. Retrieved on February 7, 2015.</ref>\n*[[Sumitomo Chemical]] - Kitahama<ref>\"[http://www.sumitomo-chem.co.jp/english/company/about/ Corporate Profile].\" [[Sumitomo Chemical]]. Retrieved on February 7, 2015.</ref>\n*[[Sumitomo Life Insurance Company]] - Shiromi (Osaka Business Park)<ref>\"[http://www.sumitomolife.co.jp/english/about/outline.html Overview].\" [[Sumitomo Life Insurance Company]]. Retrieved on February 7, 2015.</ref>\n*[[Takeda Pharmaceutical Company]]  - Dojomachi<ref>\"[http://www.takeda.com/contact/ FAQ].\" [[Takeda Pharmaceutical Company]]. Retrieved on February 2, 2011. \"Q : Where is Takeda located? A : The Head Office is located in Osaka, Japan,[...]\"</ref><ref>\"[http://www.takeda.com/about-takeda/overview/article_56.html Overview].\" Takeda Pharmaceutical Company. Retrieved on February 2, 2011. \"Headquarters Head Office 1-1, Doshomachi 4-chome, Chuo-ku, Osaka 540-8645\"</ref>\n*[[Takenaka Corporation]] - Hommachi<ref>\"[http://www.takenaka.co.jp/takenaka_e/about/profile/ Corporate Profile].\" [[Takenaka Corporation]]. Retrieved on October 20, 2009.</ref>\n*[[Teijin]] - Hommachi<ref>\"[[Teijin#cite note-TCD-1|Corporate Data]].\" [[Teijin]]. Retrieved on February 7, 2015.</ref>\n*[[Unitika]] - Kyutaro-machi<ref>\"[http://www.unitika.co.jp/e/company/group.html Unitika Group locations].\" [[Unitika]]. Retrieved on April 15, 2014.</ref>\n\n[[Sumitomo Trust and Banking]] was headquartered in Kitahama prior to its merger to form [[Sumitomo Mitsui Trust Bank]] (now headquartered in Tokyo). [[Daiwa Bank]] and [[Kinki Osaka Bank]] were headquartered in Chuo-ku prior to their merger to form [[Resona Bank]].\n\n===Branch offices===\n[[Fuji Fire and Marine]] has its Osaka offices in the ward.<ref>\"[http://www.fujikasai.co.jp/english/index.shtml Company Profile].\" ([https://archive.is/20130826153744/http://www.fujikasai.co.jp/english/index.shtml Archive]) Fuji Fire and Marine Insurance. Retrieved on August 26, 2013. \"Osaka head office: 1-18-11 Minami Senba, Chuo-ku, Osaka, Japan\" - [http://www.fujikasai.co.jp/corporate/index.shtml Information in Japanese] ([https://archive.is/20130826153952/http://www.fujikasai.co.jp/corporate/index.shtml Archive]) \"\u5927\u962a\u672c\u793e \u3012542-8567\u3000\u5927\u962a\u5e02\u4e2d\u592e\u533a\u5357\u8239\u58341\u4e01\u76ee18\u756a11\u53f7\"</ref>\n\n===Offices of foreign companies===\n[[Air China]] has an office on the 1st floor of the Uchihonmachi Green Building in Ch\u016b\u014d-ku.<ref>\"[http://www.airchina.com.cn/AboutAirChina/ContactUs/InternationalOffice/default.shtml International Offices] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081217150646/http://www.airchina.com.cn/AboutAirChina/ContactUs/InternationalOffice/default.shtml |date=2008-12-17 }}.\" ''[[Air China]]''. Retrieved on January 18, 2009.</ref> [[Asiana Airlines]] operates a sales office on the 18th Floor of the Epson Osaka Building in Ch\u016b\u014d-ku.<ref>\"[http://us.flyasiana.com/Global/US/en/homepage?cmd=&fid=ABOUT13000&region=JP&city=&searchWrd=#01 Worldwide Offices Japan] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120530193036/http://us.flyasiana.com/Global/US/en/homepage?cmd=&fid=ABOUT13000&region=JP&city=&searchWrd=%2301#01 |date=2012-05-30 }}.\" ''[[Asiana Airlines]]''. Retrieved on January 19, 2009.</ref>\n\n=== Landmarks ===\n* [[Amerikamura]]\n* [[D\u014dtonbori]]\n* [[National Bunraku Theater]]\n* [[Osaka Business Park]]\n* [[Osaka Castle]]\n* [[Shinsaibashi]]\n\n== Railway stations ==\n;[[West Japan Railway Company]] (JR West)\n:[[Osaka Loop Line]]: [[Morinomiya Station]] - [[Osakajo-koen Station]]\n;[[Keihan Electric Railway]]\n:[[Keihan Main Line|Keihan Line]]: [[Yodoyabashi Station]] - [[Kitahama Station (Osaka)|Kitahama Station]] - [[Temmabashi Station]]\n;[[Kintetsu Railway]]\n:[[Kintetsu Namba Line|Namba Line]]: [[Osaka Namba Station]] - [[Kintetsu Nippombashi Station]]\n;[[Hanshin Electric Railway]]\n:[[Hanshin Namba Line]]: Osaka Namba Station\n;[[Nankai Electric Railway]]\n:[[Nankai Main Line]]: [[Namba Station]]\n;[[Osaka Metro]]\n:[[Midosuji Line]]: [[Yodoyabashi Station]] - [[Hommachi Station]] - [[Shinsaibashi Station]] - [[Namba Station]]\n:[[Tanimachi Line]]: [[Temmabashi Station]] - [[Tanimachi Yonchome Station]] - [[Tanimachi Rokuchome Station]]\n:[[Chuo Line (Osaka)|Chuo Line]]: [[Hommachi Station]] - [[Sakaisuji-Hommachi Station]] - [[Tanimachi Yonchome Station]] - [[Morinomiya Station]]\n:[[Sennichimae Line]]: [[Namba Station]] - [[Nippombashi Station]]\n:[[Sakaisuji Line]]: [[Kitahama Station (Osaka)|Kitahama Station]] - [[Nagahoribashi Station]]\n:[[Nagahori Tsurumi-ryokuchi Line]]: [[Shinsaibashi Station]] - [[Matsuyamachi Station]] - [[Nagahoribashi Station]] - [[Tanimachi Rokuchome Station]] - (Tamatsukuri Station, Tennoji-ku) - [[Morinomiya Station]] - [[Osaka Business Park Station]]\n\n==Education==\n{{expand section|date=July 2019}}\n; Private schools\n*[[Osaka Jogakuin Junior and Senior High School]] in {{ill|Tamatsukuri|ja|\u7389\u9020 (\u5927\u962a\u5e02)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.osaka-jogakuin.ed.jp/general/schoolprofile-english.html|title=Find Out More about Us in English|publisher=[[Osaka Jogakuin Junior and Senior High School]]|accessdate=2019-07-04}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External li